        "content": "<p>Is it on purpose that <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/category_theory.category.opposite\">docs#category_theory.category.opposite</a> is not called <code>category_theory.opposite.category</code> or <code>opposite.category</code>. I just had quite a hard time finding it.</p>",
        "id": 272032404,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1644956449
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's an instance so the name should not matter.</p>",
        "id": 272032593,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1644956554
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure, but we still have a naming convention for instances.</p>",
        "id": 272032627,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1644956580
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe it works for dot notation that way?</p>",
